<div class="markdown"><h1 id="Spring-mass-harmonic-oscillator">Spring-mass harmonic oscillator</h1><h2 id="Part-one---setting-up-numerical-integration">Part one - setting up numerical integration</h2><p><em>note: there's some numerical issues that come up</em></p><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/live/Xv5swK8gwAs?si=fg7udrZ6dWFtbvNH &quot;Brachistochrone numerical integration introduction - click to watch&quot;"><img alt="Brachistochrone Numerical Integration" src="https://img.youtube.com/vi/Xv5swK8gwAs/0.jpg"/></a></p><h2 id="Part-two---getting-numerical-integration-up-and-running">Part two - getting numerical integration up and running</h2><p><em>note: ironed out some numerical issues with some hacks</em></p><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/live/fYugvp9jIUY?si=fg7udrZ6dWFtbvNH &quot;Numerical Integration - Brachistochrone and Least Action - click to watch&quot;"><img alt="Numerical Integration - Brachistochrone and Least Action" src="https://img.youtube.com/vi/fYugvp9jIUY/0.jpg"/></a></p><p>In this notebook, we solve the harmonic oscillator functions for position and velocity given the differential equation, </p><p class="tex">$$\ddot{x} = -\frac{k}{m}x$$</p><p>and initial conditions</p><p class="tex">$$x_0 = 2~m$$</p><p class="tex">$$v_0 = 0~m/s$$</p></div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>import OrdinaryDiffEq as ODE</code></pre>


<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>using Plots</code></pre>


<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>begin
    k = 100
    m = 1
    ω = sqrt(k/m)
    x0 = 2
    v0 = 0
    tspan = (0, 4*pi/ω)

    A = x0
    B = v0/ω
end</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-m">0.0</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>function harmonicoscillator(ddu, du, u, ω, t)
    ddu .= -ω^2 * u
end

#Pass to solvers</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-harmonicoscillator">harmonicoscillator (generic function with 1 method)</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>prob = ODE.SecondOrderODEProblem(harmonicoscillator, 
                                 [v0], 
                                 [x0], 
                                 tspan, 
                                 ω)</code></pre>

<div class="markdown"><h2 id="Lagrange-definition">Lagrange definition</h2><p>The <em>Principle of least action</em> states that the difference between kinetic, <span class="tex">\(T\)</span>, and potential, <span class="tex">\(V\)</span>, energy must be minimized given the forces and constraints a system. </p><p class="tex">$$L = T-V$$</p><p class="tex">$$\min_{q(t),~\dot{q}(t)} \int_{t_1}^{t_2} T(q, \dot{q})dt$$</p><p>In this case, the kinetic and potential energy is as such</p><p class="tex">$$T = \frac{1}{2}mv(t)^2$$</p><p class="tex">$$V = \frac{1}{2}kx(t)^2$$</p><p>where <span class="tex">\(x(t)\)</span> and <span class="tex">\(v(t)\)</span> are functions that we just solved for with the first differential equation. </p></div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>begin
    v = sol[1,:]
    x = sol[2,:]
    T = 1/2 .* m .* v.^2
    V = 1/2 .* k .* x.^2
    L = T .- V
    plot(t, T, label = "KE")
    plot!(t, V, label = "PE")
    plot!(t, L, label = "Action")
end</code></pre>
<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,"/>


<div class="markdown"><h2 id="Integrating-the-action-in-the-system">Integrating the <em>action</em> in the system</h2><p>In the next step, we can use the exact equations or the numerical solutions to calculate action, <span class="tex">\(L\)</span>, and integrate over the time period we considered. </p><p class="tex">$$\int_{t_1}^{t_2} T(q, \dot{q})dt \approx \sum_{i=1..N} T(q_i,\dot{q}_i)\Delta t_i$$</p><p>where <span class="tex">\(N\)</span> is the number of timesteps we solved and <span class="tex">\(\Delta t_i\)</span> is the size of each timestep. </p><p>According to the <em>principle of least action</em>, the number we calculate should be the minimum. </p></div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>function integrate_action(L, t)
    L_dt = L[1:end-1].*(t[2:end]- t[1:end-1])
    return sum(L_dt)
end</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-integrate_action">integrate_action (generic function with 1 method)</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>integrate_action(L, t)</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-hash167659">-0.5880345378239729</pre>

    v_an = ω * (-A * sin.(ω * t) + B * cos.(ω * t))
    x_an = A * cos.(ω * t) + B * sin.(ω * t)
    
    T_an = 1/2 .* m .* v_an.^2
    V_an = 1/2 .* k .* x_an.^2
    L_an = T_an .- V_an;
end</code></pre>
